God.

01:05.254 --> 01:06.255
Hello.

01:07.823 --> 01:08.824
Hi, Mom.

01:10.893 --> 01:11.894
Yeah.

01:12.995 --> 01:13.996
Thank you.

01:14.963 --> 01:17.443
Of course you're the first one.
Why wouldn't you be?

01:18.867 --> 01:21.347
Yeah, I look forward to seeing you, too.

01:22.571 --> 01:25.518
Yeah, honey, I'll see you later today. Okay.

01:28.277 --> 01:30.848
Does your mother always call you
at the crack of dawn?

01:31.246 --> 01:32.725
Only on my birthday.

01:34.249 --> 01:36.195
You didn't tell me it was your birthday.

01:36.318 --> 01:38.059
Huh. Didn't I?

01:38.387 --> 01:40.128
Well, I think I would've remembered.

01:41.557 --> 01:44.128
Okay, how old?

01:46.094 --> 01:47.095
Forty-six.

01:48.730 --> 01:50.300
Forty-six?

01:50.432 --> 01:52.241
That's not... That's not old.

01:54.303 --> 01:56.749
Okay. What are we gonna do?

01:57.072 --> 01:58.574
Shooters at The Cove, baby.

01:58.874 --> 02:03.987
My buddy hooked up with a waitress,
so if we take him, we drink for free.

02:04.580 --> 02:09.291
Okay.

02:19.494 --> 02:20.495
Senna?

02:22.698 --> 02:26.237
- Senna?
- Yeah. Hi.

02:26.368 --> 02:27.813
Theo, you better hit the road.

02:29.705 --> 02:31.026
Can we hang out again?

02:31.106 --> 02:33.450
Oh. Yeah.

02:35.077 --> 02:36.078
Hi, how's it going?

02:38.680 --> 02:40.387
So my band's playing
at The Whiskey on Saturday.

02:40.482 --> 02:42.928
Wow, that's so great.

02:46.622 --> 02:48.568
He wanted to spend my birthday with me.

02:49.124 --> 02:51.547
The nerve.
That is a relationship killer, for sure.

02:51.627 --> 02:53.916
- He's not a relationship.
- Oh. Okay.

02:53.996 --> 02:54.997
He's a hookup.

02:56.598 --> 02:59.602
And anyway, I have plans
with you on my birthday.

02:59.968 --> 03:01.777
Movies and a tattoo, right?

03:02.904 --> 03:05.227
- Who are you calling?
- My friend from Boston.

03:05.307 --> 03:06.562
The one I told you about.

03:06.642 --> 03:11.500
Recently separated,
just moved to LA, very handsome.

03:11.580 --> 03:12.581
No setups.

03:13.081 --> 03:15.721
Oh, my God!

03:16.685 --> 03:18.961
You're engaged. Why didn't you tell me?

03:20.389 --> 03:22.644
You're afraid you can't be happy
in front of me.

03:22.724 --> 03:25.295
No, I just... It wasn't a big deal. I mean...

03:25.394 --> 03:27.049
- Come on!
- Plus, it's your birthday.

03:27.129 --> 03:28.335
I was gonna wait until...

03:29.665 --> 03:31.620
You're right. It kind of makes you
wanna scream, doesn't it?

03:31.700 --> 03:33.101
Yeah.

03:37.406 --> 03:39.784
That felt good. Oh, my gosh.

03:44.146 --> 03:46.268
- He did good.
- He did, right?

03:46.348 --> 03:48.021
- You wanna try it on?
- No!

03:49.251 --> 03:52.858
Why? Are you afraid you're gonna want one?

03:53.088 --> 03:54.624
Try it on. Try it on. Try it on.

03:56.992 --> 03:59.734
Look. It doesn't fit. How metaphorical.

04:01.396 --> 04:03.740
What are you gonna do now, buy a toaster?

04:04.299 --> 04:06.822
Get towels with your name on them?
Move to the Valley?

04:06.902 --> 04:09.405
I'm gonna meet his parents.
They're flying in Friday.

04:09.705 --> 04:11.708
We're having dinner at the Highland Tower.

04:11.840 --> 04:12.841
Fancy.

04:13.575 --> 04:16.579
Look, why don't you come to work
with me, and I'll suit you up.

04:16.945 --> 04:18.390
You should get a dog.

04:19.348 --> 04:21.003
Really? And why should I get a dog?

04:21.083 --> 04:23.038
Because a dog will help you quit smoking.

04:23.118 --> 04:27.089
You smoke because you're either
lonely or unsatisfied in your life.

04:27.789 --> 04:30.929
I smoke because people are annoying.

04:31.493 --> 04:32.494
Unsatisfied then.

04:34.496 --> 04:35.839
And a dog would help me how?

04:36.398 --> 04:39.846
It's not. It was for the loneliness.
Your thing is way worse.

04:44.673 --> 04:48.712
Whether you wade through hazardous waste
or just want to look like you do,

04:49.978 --> 04:52.857
Nicoletta Fumagalli has the boot for you.

04:53.148 --> 04:54.149
Orange!

04:55.117 --> 04:59.122
It's so vibrant and holy

05:00.355 --> 05:01.343
and preppy and...

05:01.423 --> 05:03.335
Oh, you look like a lemon.

05:04.426 --> 05:08.417
I love orange.
You can color-block it like Rothko...

05:08.497 --> 05:10.204
The dinner's not in Florida.

05:11.133 --> 05:12.134
Oh. No.

05:13.368 --> 05:15.245
Yeah, there you go.

05:15.437 --> 05:17.917
- Really?
- Come on, where's the trust?

05:18.340 --> 05:19.979
Okay, okay.

05:21.042 --> 05:24.683
Those boots are an inspiration.
I'll take 'em.

05:25.113 --> 05:26.114
You're the buyer.

05:27.115 --> 05:29.027
No. Senna, no.

05:29.317 --> 05:32.093
Yes. Yes, Darla, yes.

05:32.287 --> 05:34.062
- Pins.
- Sure.

05:35.891 --> 05:37.495
- Let's see.
- Here, babe.

05:38.093 --> 05:42.405
Right. I think we just pull this in.

05:42.531 --> 05:44.686
When are you gonna design
your own line of evening wear?

05:44.766 --> 05:50.080
You know, when I get a pony and gold
medal at the Olympics for skateboarding.

05:50.472 --> 05:53.995
You can pretend you're happy hawking
other people's crappy designs,

05:54.075 --> 05:57.352
but your stoner lifestyle suggests otherwise.

05:58.780 --> 06:01.659
So let's keep this in the A-line shape.

06:02.050 --> 06:04.496
You're the Picasso of design. Look.

06:04.920 --> 06:10.063
Yeah, well, Picasso didn't have two
decades of credit card debt to pay off.

06:16.364 --> 06:18.207
- Senna.
- Mommy.

06:18.333 --> 06:19.642
My baby.

06:20.635 --> 06:23.081
My beautiful birthday girl.

06:23.638 --> 06:25.083
Just look at you.

06:25.407 --> 06:28.786
- Jack, I'd like another green tea, please.
- Absolutely.

06:30.345 --> 06:32.086
Jack asked me how old you are.

06:32.314 --> 06:35.420
- People do that on your birthday, Mom.
- When you're five.

06:37.252 --> 06:38.424
Happy birthday, baby.

06:48.663 --> 06:49.664
Open it.

06:50.932 --> 06:52.377
Oh, Mom.

06:53.101 --> 06:55.707
Your father gave that to me
on our wedding day.

06:55.971 --> 07:00.352
It brought me 10 years of the best
love any woman could ever want.

07:01.142 --> 07:03.816
Kind of hoping it'll bring you
luck in that department.

07:05.514 --> 07:06.515
Put it on.

07:08.149 --> 07:09.184
Want me to help you?

07:09.684 --> 07:10.685
Got it.

07:11.453 --> 07:13.763
There. It's beautiful on you.

07:15.257 --> 07:17.863
Um, Darla told me that you're dating a fetus.

07:18.293 --> 07:21.035
- You talked to Darla?
- So it's true.

07:21.329 --> 07:23.571
Yes, Mom, I'm dating a fetus.

07:23.965 --> 07:27.469
It's kind of hard for us to get serious
with his mom always tagging along.

07:27.903 --> 07:31.510
- Let me tell you something about men.
- Oh, please do.

07:32.207 --> 07:36.519
Men don't fall in love with women
who don't take themselves seriously.

07:37.078 --> 07:41.652
They'll have sex with them, but then
they'll have sex with just about anybody.

07:42.551 --> 07:47.330
But when it comes to love, they want
a woman who's got her act together.

07:50.025 --> 07:56.636
I'm trying to acknowledge that
without sarcasm, but it's hard.

07:56.765 --> 08:00.304
Don't eat the bread.
If you're hungry, we'll order.

08:00.869 --> 08:03.577
By the way, just asking.

08:04.339 --> 08:06.928
What image do you think you project

08:07.008 --> 08:09.511
when you wear a top that you can see through?

08:10.245 --> 08:13.249
- It's Christian Dior, Mom.
- I don't care who it is.

08:14.115 --> 08:16.527
Showing your nipples
doesn't make you look chic.

08:16.718 --> 08:18.755
It just makes you look like a tart.

08:36.837 --> 08:38.078
Senna, come in.

08:41.509 --> 08:43.648
I have just one question.

08:44.946 --> 08:48.003
Are you kidding me?
Do you know who my customers are?

08:48.083 --> 08:50.839
Have you seen them?
Have you noticed what they're wearing?

08:50.919 --> 08:53.399
- Yes. The boot...
- Is orange!

08:53.822 --> 08:55.911
- Well, I thought...
- I know what you thought.

08:55.991 --> 08:59.063
That it would be fun and unique and daring.

08:59.361 --> 09:00.704
My customers are not daring!

09:00.829 --> 09:02.951
And it's not your job to reinvent them.

09:03.031 --> 09:05.409
It's your job to buy what they want to wear.

09:07.302 --> 09:09.491
I can't keep having
this conversation with you.

09:09.571 --> 09:11.676
I'm sorry, but we're done.

09:12.707 --> 09:15.882
- What do you mean?
- I mean you're fired.

09:22.984 --> 09:25.974
- You said we were staying in.
- I just ordered a ton of takeout,

09:26.054 --> 09:27.576
and I need help carrying it out.

09:27.656 --> 09:30.679
- It's really good.
- Surprise!

09:30.759 --> 09:31.760
Happy birthday!

09:32.861 --> 09:37.867
<i>Happy birthday, dear Senna</i>

09:38.933 --> 09:44.406
<i>Happy birthday to you</i>

09:44.739 --> 09:46.946
- Make a wish.
- Don't waste it.

09:52.280 --> 09:53.281
Come on!

10:01.056 --> 10:03.712
- Senna!
- Lars.

10:03.792 --> 10:06.773
I got you something. It's on the house.

10:06.928 --> 10:09.135
Happy, happy birthday.

10:11.633 --> 10:12.634
Okay.

10:13.001 --> 10:14.002
Up-up-up.

10:14.202 --> 10:16.773
- Gonna need to see some ID.
- Oh, you.

10:16.971 --> 10:17.972
Mmm.

10:18.173 --> 10:20.595
- Sore subject?
- Little bit.

10:20.675 --> 10:23.698
Mmm. How about you, bud?
Can I get you something?

10:23.778 --> 10:27.726
Um... A frozen strawberry daiquiri, please.

10:29.451 --> 10:31.522
- Seriously?
- Seriously.

10:34.089 --> 10:36.968
It's the palm trees.
They make me feel like I'm on vacation.

10:38.059 --> 10:41.598
- Where are you from?
- Boston. Yeah.

10:42.263 --> 10:46.487
I moved out here a week ago.
I'm hoping to get discovered.

10:47.767 --> 10:50.213
Really? Actor or rock star?

10:51.106 --> 10:52.107
Rock star, obviously.

10:53.308 --> 10:56.221
- So what do you play?
- Nothing yet.

10:56.978 --> 11:00.323
It's really more of a backup plan
in case my day job doesn't work out.

11:01.182 --> 11:04.095
- What do you do?
- I'm a lawyer.

11:04.252 --> 11:05.253
Oh.

11:05.420 --> 11:08.299
My firm has offices out here.
They offered to relocate me,

11:09.624 --> 11:12.380
and I didn't want to turn down
a free trip to California.

11:12.460 --> 11:17.535
Well, when the inner rock star
beckons, better listen.

11:17.632 --> 11:19.771
You know what? That is so true.

11:20.468 --> 11:23.540
And my inner rock star
is extremely temperamental.

11:24.205 --> 11:28.085
One frozen strawberry daiquiri,
extra umbrella for you.

11:28.176 --> 11:29.951
Wow, thank you.

11:30.645 --> 11:32.147
So where are you squatting?

11:33.281 --> 11:34.282
Santa Monica.

11:34.916 --> 11:37.672
That is a long way to come for a daiquiri.

11:37.752 --> 11:41.700
It was. I'm supposed to meet someone
I knew from Boston, a woman I worked with.

11:42.290 --> 11:44.736
She's having a birthday party
for a friend of hers.

11:45.026 --> 11:48.283
Sei... Set... Sierra? Sierra or Henna.

11:48.363 --> 11:51.742
Some hippie, crunchy name
you only hear in California.

11:52.367 --> 11:54.711
I'm actually kind of relieved
I missed the party.

11:55.870 --> 11:58.544
Really? And why is that?

11:58.807 --> 12:00.695
- My friend Darla...
- Mmm-hmm.

12:00.775 --> 12:02.687
She kind of fancies herself as a matchmaker.

12:03.478 --> 12:05.967
- Does she? Uh-huh.
- Mmm-hmm.

12:06.047 --> 12:08.618
- And I hate to be set up.
- You do?

12:08.817 --> 12:10.972
Don't you? It's awful.

12:11.052 --> 12:12.759
So why'd you do it?

12:13.688 --> 12:14.689
She begged.

12:16.491 --> 12:19.267
- She begged?
- She kind of did.

12:19.427 --> 12:21.407
She begged!

12:22.897 --> 12:23.898
Oh.

12:24.499 --> 12:25.842
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

12:26.634 --> 12:27.989
- Her friend...
- Uh-huh.

12:28.069 --> 12:29.946
Kind of sounds like a train wreck.

12:30.939 --> 12:33.328
Yeah, she went to art school
for a couple of years.

12:33.408 --> 12:36.321
That obviously didn't work out,
and now she's working some...

12:36.945 --> 12:39.585
I don't know. Some kind of,
like, nowhere job in retail.

12:40.849 --> 12:45.161
She just sounds really unhappy,
like she's floundering around, so...

12:45.687 --> 12:49.635
So you don't really want to get set up.
You wanted a hookup.

12:51.359 --> 12:52.580
Yeah! You met her! Look at you!

12:52.660 --> 12:54.449
You're here! I looked all over for you.

12:54.529 --> 12:57.510
Oh, well, I am very small.
You have to look hard.

12:58.499 --> 13:00.502
I see that you've met Senna.

13:01.636 --> 13:05.015
- Not officially.
- Okay, well, let me do the honors.

13:05.206 --> 13:07.209
- Adam, this is Senna.
- Hi, Senna.

13:07.508 --> 13:09.030
Senna, this is Adam from Boston.

13:09.110 --> 13:11.466
We worked together briefly
during my confused period.

13:11.546 --> 13:15.653
He is a lawyer, but he has many
other attractive qualities.

13:16.818 --> 13:21.324
It was four years at FIDM
and a masters at Parsons,

13:21.689 --> 13:25.246
but I did get fired today
from that nowhere job,

13:25.326 --> 13:29.001
so I am officially
an unemployed hippie hookup.

13:29.430 --> 13:32.387
- I am so sorry. I had no idea.
- Wait. What? You're not a hippie.

13:32.467 --> 13:35.312
- You know what? I'm gonna go.
- Wait, what did I miss?

13:35.436 --> 13:36.891
I got these, okay?

13:36.971 --> 13:38.143
What did you talk about?

13:38.840 --> 13:39.828
Keep the change.

13:39.908 --> 13:42.320
- Adam!
- I'll call you, okay?

13:43.144 --> 13:44.933
What? What just happened?

13:45.013 --> 13:47.391
- I just said no setups.
- Okay, I'm sorry.

13:47.815 --> 13:49.317
Did you just say you got fired?

13:50.318 --> 13:51.695
Oh, God. Today?

13:52.320 --> 13:55.324
Oh, no. I'm sorry. But you know what?

13:55.757 --> 14:00.114
That's good because now you can start
your career as a designer.

14:00.194 --> 14:03.017
Yeah, people just wake up and say,

14:03.097 --> 14:05.453
"You know what? I'm gonna
start a new career today

14:05.533 --> 14:11.292
"because I have startup capital
and distribution and marketing..."

14:11.372 --> 14:13.761
Blah-blah-blah-blah. Negativity!

14:13.841 --> 14:16.253
You know what you are?
You're a raisin in the sun.

14:16.511 --> 14:19.890
- I'm a raisin?
- You are a talented, terrified raisin

14:20.048 --> 14:23.962
festering in your own self-doubt.
But I believe in you.

14:24.118 --> 14:26.274
I've always believed in you.
I believe in you.

14:26.354 --> 14:31.429
<i>I believe, I believe, I believe, I believe</i>

14:31.759 --> 14:33.432
<i>I believe in you</i>

14:33.561 --> 14:35.483
<i>Senna, I believe in you</i>

14:35.563 --> 14:37.886
<i>Everybody, I believe in you</i>

14:37.966 --> 14:40.021
<i>Lars, I believe in you</i>

14:40.101 --> 14:41.089
<i>Come on!</i>

14:41.169 --> 14:42.156
<i>I believe in you</i>

14:42.236 --> 14:43.758
<i>I don't see hands I believe in...</i>

14:43.838 --> 14:45.260
Okay, okay, it's a serious moment.

14:45.340 --> 14:47.582
I'm kidding. I'll get my purse! Just wait!

15:02.423 --> 15:03.424
Senna.

15:04.692 --> 15:07.468
Forgive me. Darla didn't beg.

15:08.696 --> 15:09.731
I wanted to come.

15:10.465 --> 15:13.344
When I walked in and I didn't
see her, I felt like an idiot.

15:13.568 --> 15:14.877
I was on my way out.

15:16.304 --> 15:18.477
Then I saw you sitting
at the bar by yourself.

15:20.408 --> 15:23.164
I just... I didn't want you to think I was
the kind of guy who needed a setup.

15:23.244 --> 15:25.247
It was stupid. I'm so sorry.

15:28.349 --> 15:29.350
It's cool.

15:33.654 --> 15:34.963
Happy birthday.

15:36.090 --> 15:37.091
Thanks.

15:46.034 --> 15:49.379
<i>What did I wish for?
You know I can't tell you that.</i>

15:49.937 --> 15:54.113
No, not a man or my name up in lights

15:55.276 --> 15:57.620
or bring back people from the dead

15:58.446 --> 16:02.019
or a pile of money on my doorstep,
though that would be nice.

16:03.418 --> 16:05.921
No, truth is, I'm good right where I am.

16:06.821 --> 16:10.645
I mean, little things would be nice,
like a flawless complexion,

16:10.725 --> 16:15.197
or my mother stopped making me
feel like I'm a disappointment to her.

16:17.165 --> 16:19.941
But I didn't waste my wish on those things.

16:31.112 --> 16:32.113
Hello?

16:34.315 --> 16:35.316
Yeah.

16:37.351 --> 16:39.831
Of course you're the first to call, Mom.

16:40.455 --> 16:42.401
It's the middle of the night.

16:46.227 --> 16:47.228
Thanks, Mom.

16:48.763 --> 16:49.764
I love you, too.

16:57.672 --> 17:00.209
- What's up?
- Sorry.

17:03.111 --> 17:04.750
I got some pancakes over here.

17:05.079 --> 17:06.455
Want some coffee?

17:08.316 --> 17:10.387
I forgot she was staying with you.

17:18.759 --> 17:21.035
- That's a good one. Yeah.
- Oh, wow.

17:22.029 --> 17:25.532
- Oh, I love this one.
- You can't have that. I need to sell that.

17:26.467 --> 17:28.656
You don't want me to live here
forever, do you?

17:28.736 --> 17:29.737
No. Good point.

17:31.873 --> 17:35.396
- <i>Bonjour, bonjour!</i>
- Oh, no. No, no, no.

17:35.476 --> 17:36.853
Yes, yes, yes!

17:37.712 --> 17:38.884
You're gonna love these.

17:39.180 --> 17:41.302
I already love the 14 you already brought me.

17:41.382 --> 17:44.989
Yes, but you said they weren't selling,
so I made some more.

17:46.821 --> 17:48.664
Look at this.

17:52.193 --> 17:54.833
- Jean-Michel!
- Dede!

17:54.996 --> 17:55.997
I have five minutes.

17:58.366 --> 18:00.121
- Show me something I have to have.
- This is kismet.

18:00.201 --> 18:03.011
Dede Zeller, meet Senna Berges.

18:04.038 --> 18:06.360
If she likes you, the world likes you.

18:06.440 --> 18:09.182
- Congratulations on your new store.
- Stores.

18:09.644 --> 18:10.645
Stores!

18:11.412 --> 18:12.413
Mmm.

18:13.781 --> 18:16.037
- Are these yours?
- Yes. They're prototypes.

18:16.117 --> 18:20.156
I have 21 that I've made so far.

18:20.688 --> 18:23.863
- Who's carrying them?
- Well, no one yet.

18:24.125 --> 18:26.380
- So you're in production?
- Well, no.

18:26.460 --> 18:29.717
I mean, I didn't know which ones
would catch on, so I just made them,

18:29.797 --> 18:32.744
and I thought I'd make more
when we see how they go.

18:34.769 --> 18:37.658
But, you know, I could design
exclusively for you

18:37.738 --> 18:42.330
for a little while or for
a long while, if you like.

18:42.410 --> 18:44.287
- I need to see those coats.
- Sure.

18:45.513 --> 18:46.514
Here.

18:49.217 --> 18:50.821
<i>Have you sold any of your purses?</i>

18:52.185 --> 18:55.743
Well, I had a meeting
with Dede Zeller this morning.

18:55.823 --> 18:58.736
- And?
- She seemed interested.

18:58.960 --> 19:02.183
Well, you have to stay on it. Be aggressive.

19:02.263 --> 19:03.435
I'm on it, Mom.

19:07.668 --> 19:08.669
Oh.

19:10.104 --> 19:11.674
You got me a place setting.

19:11.906 --> 19:15.354
Well, I believe every woman
should have a set of fine china.

19:15.843 --> 19:19.901
Since it doesn't look like you're ever gonna
get married, I thought I'd better start now.

19:19.981 --> 19:22.689
In 11 years, you'll have a complete set.

